headline.main: Effect of Statement; China Aided, but Renewed Japanese Resistance Is Seen in Cairo Stand

lead_paragraph: The revelation last night that President Roosevelt, Prime Minister Churchill and Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek, meeting in Cairo, had agreed that Japan must give up all territory taken "by violence and greed," is probably only the first of a series of momentous announcements.
abstract: H W Baldwin on conf decisions
